---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Make Failures Explicit and Understandable"
  description="When the AI fails or produces wrong output, make it clear that something went wrong and explain what happened in user-facing terms."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Explicit failure messaging" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full">
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Clear Error Message</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >The AI couldn't complete the analysis. The service is temporarily unavailable. Your
            data was not sent.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Users know: something failed, why (service unavailable), and that their data is safe.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-button variant="outline" size="sm">Try again</mds-button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-status-error-10 border border-status-error-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-200">
            <mds-icon name="mi/outline/error" class="text-status-error-05"></mds-icon>
            <mds-text typography="label"><b>Vague or Hidden Failure (Problematic)</b></mds-text>
          </div>
          <mds-text typography="body">Something went wrong. Error code: 0x7F3A</mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-status-error-06"
            >Technical codes and vague wording don't help users understand what failed or what to
            do.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-400 p-600 rounded-lg bg-tone-neutral-09 border border-tone-neutral-03">
        <div class="grid gap-200">
          <mds-text typography="label"><b>When AI Output Is Wrong</b></mds-text>
          <mds-text typography="body"
            >This translation may be inaccurate. The source text contains uncommon terms I'm not
            confident about. Please verify before using.</mds-text
          >
          <mds-text typography="caption" class="text-tone-neutral-05"
            >Explicitly signal uncertainty or possible error so users don't trust wrong output.</mds-text
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      State clearly when the AI failed or when output may be wrong.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Hide failures behind vague messages or technical error codes only.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Explain what went wrong in user-facing language and what it means for the user.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">Let wrong or failed outputs appear as if they succeeded.</UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
